Map data

  The Docker images published from this project embed databases derived from
  OpenStreetMap data: Valhalla routing tiles and a Photon geocoding index.

  Map data (c) OpenStreetMap contributors, available under the Open Database
  License (ODbL) 1.0: https://opendatacommons.org/licenses/odbl/1-0/
  OSM extracts are downloaded from Geofabrik: https://download.geofabrik.de/

  These derivative databases are themselves made available under ODbL 1.0.
  Per ODbL section 4.6, the full derivative databases are the freely pullable
  images at ghcr.io/roma8ok/getmapstack/{country}, and the method of creating
  them is the public build pipeline in build/valhalla/ and build/photon/
  applied to the Geofabrik extracts above.

  If you publicly use routing or geocoding results from these images (for
  example in an application or on a map), you must credit OpenStreetMap:
  "(c) OpenStreetMap contributors" with a link to
  https://www.openstreetmap.org/copyright
  See: https://osmfoundation.org/wiki/Licence/Attribution_Guidelines

Third-party software

  The published images also bundle third-party software components (Valhalla,
  prime_server, Photon, Ubuntu packages). Their license texts ship inside
